The paper deals with combinatorial objects such as words and palindromes, and uses techniques from discrete mathematics and information theory to study their properties. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of asymptotic behavior, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper uses results from the theory of borders, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with the study of square prefixes, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
